lab 8
pg 531; #15.15

(Using JScrollBar) Write a program that uses scroll bars to select the
foreground color for a label, as shown in Figure 15.47. Three horizontal scroll
bars are used for selecting the red, green, and blue components of the color.
Use a title border on the panel that holds the scroll bars.

    Figure 15.47

    +----------------------------------------------------+
    | Exercise15_15                               _ O X  |
    |----------------------------------------------------|
    |                                                    |
    |                    Show Colors                 <--------[ Pane with BorderLayout]
    |                                                    |
    | +- Choose colors --------------------------------+ |
    | |        +------------------------------------+  | |
    | | Red    | <|------------|||---------------|> |  | |
    | |        |                                    |  | |
    | | Green  | <|---|||------------------------|> |  | |
    | |        |                                    | <-------[ Panel with GridLayout for three scroll bars ]
    | | Blue   | <|--------------------|||-------|> |  | |
    | |   ^    +------------------------------------+  | |
    | +---|--------------------------------------------+ |
    +-----|----------------------------------------------+
          |
 [ Panel with GridLayout for three labels ]
